body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

I came across the following assertion failure while trying to determine if a particular CRC was programmed properly.  In this case, I was given a message as well as what the CRC for the message should've been, and I was trying to make certain that they matched.

Here's the code:

```verilog
module	fnmcve(o_crc);
	output	reg	[7:0]	o_crc;

	always @(*)
		o_crc = gencrc({ 2'b01, 6'h11, 32'h00 });

	function [7:0]	gencrc;
		input	[39:0]	i_cmdword;
		integer	icrc;

		gencrc = 0;
		for(icrc=0; icrc<40; icrc=icrc+1)
		if (i_cmdword[39-icrc] ^ gencrc[7])
			gencrc[7:1] = { gencrc[6:1], 1'b0 } ^ 7'h09;
		else
			gencrc[7:1] = { gencrc[6:1], 1'b0 };
		gencrc = { gencrc[7:1], 1'b1 };
	endfunction
endmodule
```
When you evaluate this code with `yosys -qp 'read -formal fnmcve.v'` you get the following error:

```
$ yosys -qp 'read -formal fnmcve.v'
ERROR: Assert `block == NULL' failed in frontends/ast/simplify.cc:3471.
```

I have tested this on the current version on github.  It fails with the open source parser, but not with the Verific enabled parser.

## Expected behavior

No internal assertion failure

## Actual behavior

See above.

